The paper deals with query optimization in SPARQL, which is a query language for RDF data. This falls under the domain of databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as SPARQL is used for querying knowledge graphs. The paper also discusses heuristics-based query optimization, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and deep learning (cs.DL). Finally, the paper proposes a method that can be applied to existing SPARQL implementations, which falls under the domain of software engineering (cs.SE).
